         <abstract>
            <p>In this note, we consider the backward errors for more general inverse eigenvalue problems by extending Sun's approach. The optimal backward errors are defined for diagonalization matrix inverse eigenvalue problem with respect to an approximate solution, and the upper and lower bounds are derived for the optimal backward errors. The results may be useful for testing the stability of practical algorithms.</p>
